OL,3,C'The shelling took away my whole
OL,4,Cfamily'
OL,6,F"I didn't expect the destruction to be
OL,7,Flike this. I can't believe it. It's so
OL,8,Fawful."
OL,10,FMaha is looking out the window of the
OL,11,Fvehicle carrying her through what's
OL,12,Fleft of her old neighbourhood.
OL,14,FPiles of rubble that used to be
OL,15,Fbuildings line the roads.
OL,17,FShe is 33 but her eyes look older,
OL,18,Ftired, frightened.
