OL,3,C'The shelling took away my whole
OL,4,Cfamily'
OL,6,FShe climbs the stairs up to her old
OL,7,Fapartment and, between sobs, points
OL,8,Fout of the hole in the wall.
OL,10,F"This is where I saw my son... and
OL,11,Fthere is where my husband and my kids
OL,12,Fwere".
OL,14,FOn the 24th April Maha's life changed
OL,15,Fforever.
OL,17,F"I was in the kitchen. I was preparing
OL,18,Ffood. No one told us anything. The
OL,19,Fexplosion just happened."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
